local currentTurkeys = 0
--math.randomseed(string.len(newPlayer.Name) % 5 * math.random(newPlayer.userId / 2, newPlayer.userId * 2))
local tShooter = script.Parent
function turkeyTouched(part, turkey) if part == nil or (part.Parent == nil) then return end hum = part.Parent:FindFirstChild("Humanoid") if hum ~= nil then if turkey.Name == "Turkey1" then hum:TakeDamage(1) elseif turkey.Name == "Turkey2" then hum:TakeDamage(2) else hum:TakeDamage(5) end end end
function stick(x, y) weld = Instance.new("Weld")
weld.Part0 = x weld.Part1 = y
local HitPos = x.Position
local CJ = CFrame.new(HitPos) local C0 = x.CFrame:inverse() * CJ local C1 = y.CFrame:inverse() * CJ
weld.C0 = C0 weld.C1 = C1
weld.Parent = x end
tShooter.Enabled = true function spawnTurkey() if currentTurkeys < 5 and tShooter.Enabled then tShooter.Enabled = false randomInt = math.random(0, 100) if randomInt < 51 then turkeyType = 1 elseif randomInt < 86 then turkeyType = 2 else turkeyType = 3 end local newTurkey = tShooter.Handle:findFirstChild("Turkey".. turkeyType):clone() newTurkey.Parent = game.Workspace newTurkey:moveTo(tShooter.Handle.Position + tShooter.Handle.CFrame:vectorToWorldSpace(Vector3.new(0, -1, 0)).unit*5) -- + Vector3.new(0,2,0)) local base = newTurkey.Base g = newTurkey:getChildren() for i = 1, #g do if g[i].className == "Part" and g[i] ~= base then stick(base, g[i]) g[i].Touched:connect(function(touched) turkeyTouched(touched, newTurkey) end) end end for i = 1, #g do if g[i].className == "Part" then g[i].Anchored = false if g[i].Name ~= "Base" then g[i].CanCollide = true g[i].Transparency = 0 end end end
tShooter.Handle.CakeBang:Play() tShooter.Handle.TurkeySound:Play()
if turkeyType > 1 then newTurkey.Body.Sparkles.Enabled = true end
base.BodyGyro.cframe = base.CFrame
base.Velocity = tShooter.Handle.CFrame:vectorToWorldSpace(Vector3.new(0, -1, 0)).unit*200 + Vector3.new(0, 50, 0)
currentTurkeys = currentTurkeys + 1 tShooter.Enabled = true
wait(10) currentTurkeys = currentTurkeys - 1 newTurkey:remove()
end end
function onEquip() tShooter.Handle.TurkeySound.Volume = 1 tShooter.Handle.CakeBang.Volume = 1 end
function onUnequip() tShooter.Handle.TurkeySound.Volume = 0 tShooter.Handle.CakeBang.Volume = 0 end
tShooter.Activated:connect(spawnTurkey) tShooter.Equipped:connect(onEquip) tShooter.Unequipped:connect(onUnequip)

base = script.Parent.Base math.randomseed(tick()) wait(1) while true do targetPos = Vector3.new(math.random(base.Position.X - 20, base.Position.X + 20), script.Parent.GroundHeight.Value, math.random(base.Position.Z - 20, base.Position.Z + 20)) base.BodyPosition.position = targetPos base.CFrame = CFrame.new(base.Position, -targetPos) wait(1) end

base = script.Parent.Base math.randomseed(tick()) wait(1) while true do targetPos = Vector3.new(math.random(base.Position.X - 25, base.Position.X + 25), script.Parent.GroundHeight.Value + 0.5, math.random(base.Position.Z - 25, base.Position.Z + 25)) base.BodyPosition.position = targetPos base.CFrame = CFrame.new(base.Position, -targetPos) wait(1) end

base = script.Parent.Base math.randomseed(tick()) wait(1) while true do targetPos = Vector3.new(math.random(base.Position.X - 30, base.Position.X + 30), script.Parent.GroundHeight.Value + 0.5, math.random(base.Position.Z - 30, base.Position.Z + 30)) base.BodyPosition.position = targetPos base.CFrame = CFrame.new(base.Position, -targetPos) wait(1) end
